snippet.textDisplay:
Big takeaways for PSG:
- Won without Verratti, Silva, Meunier, Herrera, and only had Mbappe for around 20-30 minutes.
- Most of the MOTM candidates were defenders, which is very good to see. We all know PSG's attack is world class, so to see players like Bernat, Kimpembe, Kehrer, Gueye, and Marquinhos step up so big is what we need to go deeper.
- Won without a home crowd.
- Kept a clean sheet against an attack that was widely predicted to easily score at least 1 or 2 goals. Amazing.

If you wish to prepare for the coronavirus I personally suggest the following;

Buy some extra food, water, medicine, and necessities for your self and family.
Sell what you need to, cut out media monthly payments such as Netflix, Pandora, YouTube, Hulu, Roku, Disney+, satellite radio etc. Unplug Wifi and turn off computer at night to reduce and prevent 5g and wireless radiation exposure. Clean your house of unnecessary junk to remove mental clutter and chaos, call or write everyone you know and tell them you love them and reflect on a favorite memory, write a list of everything you've been grateful for in this life, try to remain calm and meditate if theres nothing one can do in the moment. Otherwise go enjoy your life to the fullest while you have it.
